title: Papeete
summary: Papeete (pronounced [pa.pe.Ê”e.te])[3] is the capital city of French Polynesia, an overseas collectivity of the French Republic in the Pacific Ocean. The commune of Papeete is located on the island of Tahiti, in the administrative subdivision of the Windward Islands, of which Papeete is the administrative capital.[4] The French High Commissioner also resides in Papeete.[5]
